Acciona, Criteria, Gamesa, Repsol, Zon: Iberian Equity Preview

-- B y   C h a r l e s   P e n t y
-- 
2011-05-12T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/acciona-criteria-gamesa-repsol-zon-iberian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish and Portuguese trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index (IBEX)  rose 0.6 percent to 10,531.50.
Portugal’s  PSI-20 Index (PSI20)  gained 0.7 percent to 7,773.46.  Spanish stocks:  Acciona SA (ANA)  : Spain’s second-biggest wind-farm owner
will report first-quarter earnings before the market opens in
Madrid. The shares fell 0.2 percent to 75.14 euros.  Clinica Baviera SA (CBAV)  : The eye clinics company said
in a filing its first-quarter net income rose to 2.45 million
euros ($3.48 million) from 2.3 million euros a year earlier. The
shares jumped 6.8 percent to 8.62 euros.  Criteria CaixaCorp SA (CRI)  : The investment holding
company of the La Caixa savings bank group will hold its annual
 shareholders’ meeting  in Barcelona. The shares rose 1.8 percent
to 5.06 euros.  Gamesa Corporacion Tecnologica SA (GAM SM):  Spain ’s largest
wind-turbine maker will report first-quarter earnings after the
market closes in Madrid. The shares rose 0.3 percent to 6.24
euros.  Indra Sistemas SA (IDR)  : Spain’s largest computer
services company will report first-quarter earnings. The shares
fell 1.4 percent to 15.58 euros.  Obrascon Huarte Lain SA (OHL)  : The builder will report
first-quarter earnings before the market opens in Madrid. The
shares dropped 1.9 percent to 26.10 euros.  Repsol YPF SA (REP)  : The oil company will report first-
quarter earnings before the market opens in Madrid. Repsol may
say first-quarter profit excluding some items rose to 551
million euros from 508 million euros a year earlier, according
to the average estimate in a Bloomberg survey of 15 analysts.
The shares fell 0.2 percent to 23.09 euros.  Portuguese stocks:  Altri SGPS SA (ALTR)  : Portugal’s second-biggest pulp-
and-paper producer said first-quarter profit increased to 9.22
million euros. The shares gained 2.4 percent to 1.69 euros.  Zon Multimedia SGPS SA (ZON PL): Portugal’s biggest cable-
television company is scheduled to report first-quarter earnings
before the 8:00 a.m. market open. The shares fell 0.8 percent to
3.66 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
